cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PL, cs.LO 

This paper discusses access control models and authorization policy languages, which are relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions attribute-based access control systems, which are related to database systems (cs.DB) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper presents a formal framework for access control, which involves logic and reasoning (cs.LO).
